caption: I told my friends about this restaurant with my warmest recommendations. I go their often. This recommendation is always successful. The dishes they serve are yummy and the crew is welcoming and cooperative. Whenever we go to this place we enjoy a cheerful time.  highly recommended.
Good sandwiches for a quick bite. Falafel was amazing and the shawarma was good...huge servings.
This restaurant provides superb service and enjoyable menu. One of the best restaurant in the area. The food and drinks came out quick and the rates were economical. I recommend this place.
The meals and service were ahead of my expectations. I really liked the ambience of this restaurant. Excellent spot to take my family out for dinner.
Nice clean establishment with good food
The beef/lamb and chicken shawarma plates are amazing. Portion size is great. As someone who enjoys original Arabic flavours, this is a hidden gem.
Try this place. You won't regrets

I just had an order delivered and the phone is soooo good! I got the beef and lamb shawarma plate and not only was everything in the plate is delicious, you get a decent proportion. I will recommend this restaurant to everyone I know!
Great food Reasonable prices Great customer service Big difference between this one and san bruno lotus
This food was amazing! The staff was wonderful & very accommodating. Definitely coming back.
I've only tasted the falafel plate and it was delicious, other than that I don't know
Fast service
Good price good Falafel. In this area it is likely the best
Excellent falafel
The falafelmsandwich is good

Excellent place!!! They are fairly quick and getting the dishes ordered. Small place but  food ia good. House special stands out and  you'll never regret. Quantity is huge and fills your tummy full 😉 Their rice is heavy and you can't …

Orders come quick -  no doubt about that. Frequent choice for the business crowd in the area. Food is okay - this review is based on the chicken which was drier than I liked and $$ to quantity higher than I liked.
Fantastic food!  If you haven't had shawerma before make sure and give  it a try!
Fantastic!
This place rocks!  People are great and food is fabulous
Great delivery. Nothing terribly special, but ordering in is super easy with this place.
Food here is consistently good, with large portions. Only downside is that it can get busy at lunchtime if you don't get there early.
Tasty food that's prepared quickly with friendly service
Falafel are both moist and crispy, a rare find! Hands down the best Falafel in the area there is no comparison.
Easy, fast, delicious. ~$13 for chicken shawarma
Good food fast service

Oddly enough they make a very good cheeseburger and Mediterranean burger one if the best in the area. It comes with fries and a soda. The other items are quite tasty as well. Very well seasoned and the portions are a nice size.
Love this place. Great food & free refills!
Stuff behavior is unprofessional and very disrespectful. Service quality is equal to zero. I wouldn't not recommend to any one .
Great food.  Reasonably priced.
I suggest you to order special dish, it comes with homus, flafel , rice, salad, and chicken
Had a delicious halal lamb over rice plate - generous portions, great value!
Amazing Med food. Clean environment. Would definitely go back!

Order the hummus, it was tasty. I did not like the fact that it did not come with at least one pitta bread. Most Mediterranean restaurants I go to the Pita bread comes with the hummus but not here, the bread is an extra $1.50. The bread was cold also. I am used to hot pitta bread and cold hummus. The contrast in temp is palletable.
Great
Very good! Had the falafel wrap and a side of fries. Just enough food and not too messy. Be sure to ask for extra sauce!
Delicious,  fast and fresh,  as usual.  Best falafel and hummus ever!  Everything I've eaten there is delicious.  Even when catered!
Great!

First time trying out this place, loved it! You can see them cooking the meat on the spot for you & then straight to your plate, it can’t get fresher than that! I got myself the Chicken & Lamb Sherwarma over rice plate, they give you a big …

nice little family run eatery, on my first visit I wasn't disappointed.  I got the combo shwarma over rice, meat was tender & well done, but a bit dry to my liking. I felt this dish needs a side of greens & a small side of yogurt  and some fresh mint!
Always great freshly made food here never disappoints

Best shawerma wrap I've had in years - possibly ever. Perfect and delicious in every way - spices, fresh ingredients, everything on point. My only minor quibble is the wrap is too thin and all the deliciousness kept falling out - but that's a minor quibble. Get thee to Lotus, stat!

I am rating them 1 star as I went at 2 pm and I found them closed even the sign on the door said that they close at 3 pm, So please if you are not going to be open change the sign on the door so people won’t was their time combing all the way to find you closed

Great family owned business. Faster service than anywhere else in Oakland: for the amazing quality of food you get. Authentic taste for most dishes. Fresh, delicious food, combined with amazing customer service. Not much more one could ask for.

Went with  few colleagues for lunch to try different things.  Lunchtime is a busy time for them which may explain the missteps we noted. The menu focuses on standard middle eastern menu with falafel and shawarmas and the like.  The process …

Excellent shawarma, I will continue to come back again and again! The falafel is also excellent. The one thing I don't like is the hummus; there's something about it that just isn't my favorite. That said, the other sides (tabouleh, mediterranean salad, and baba ganoush) are all delicious.

Some people might find this place too "ethnic" or "authentic".  To me, it is just delicious.  The baba ghanoush is crazy good.  The half chicken is tender and juicy.  Service is friendly, veggies are fresh, and spices are on point.
I.lobe it!
Good Mediterranean food and affordable price.

Got the lentil soup and the stuffed grape leaves. Meh. Soup looked more like pea soup and too salty. If they can't get these staples right, the rest is questionable. Cost was about $9. Too expensive to go back.
(Translated by Google) Yummy shewarma and falafel.  (Original) Yummy shewarma and falafel.
Best falafel spot in Oakland

I had the pick 2 combo - I chose chicken kabob and kefta kabob. The beef was delicious but the chicken was not cooked throughly.   I was disappointed but will give it another try.  Also wish they were open in weekends.
Great food resonably priced.
Yummy falafel wraps and gyros!  LOVE the beef/lamb shawerma.  Quick and affordable.
Having grown up in Middle East, I have pretty high standards regarding food from the region.  I absolutely love this place!
They have different food to chose from. I Wish they have a menus to go option.
Randomly found this place. Food was delicious
Unbelievable beef and lamb plate. I've had this dish everywhere I can find it for the past 10 years and this is absolutely the best place for it.
Great place to Meditteran food. Sandwiches are really good.
their hummus is awesome, and their halal burgers are excellent and the kabobs may be the best I've tasted.
Small, fast, massive portions.
Flavorful beef and lamb shawarma over rice, and a generous portion, too. I'm making this a regular lunch spot.
Great food, solid value, quick. Perfect lunch spot.
The best mediterraean food i have ever had!!

Absolutely delicious!  I had this place for lunch yesterday and I was amazed how delicious it was.  They give you all the ingredients in separate boxes so you can then make your falafel your self. We had enough for four people.  I was very …
